95
00:07:29,212 --> 00:07:30,954
Yeah, but she will.

96
00:07:31,603 --> 00:07:33,243
I want us to live together.

97
00:07:34,010 --> 00:07:36,371
I want to be your husband again, Haley.

98
00:07:38,667 --> 00:07:40,978
That sounds so good to me.

99
00:07:42,310 --> 00:07:44,213
But I have a roommate named Brooke.

100
00:07:44,214 --> 00:07:45,305
That doesn't matter.

101
00:07:45,306 --> 00:07:48,062
And our dream schools are 3,000 miles away.

102
00:07:48,063 --> 00:07:48,899
Doesn't matter.

103
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:50,363
And neither of us have jobs.

104
00:07:50,364 --> 00:07:51,784
It doesn't matter.

105
00:07:51,956 --> 00:07:54,122
You know how long it took me to realize that?

106
00:07:54,584 --> 00:07:56,903
The amount of time it takes to pull a trigger.

107
00:07:58,770 --> 00:08:02,953
I love you, Haley James, and that's all I need to know.

108
00:08:03,265 --> 00:08:05,662
That doesn't mean it's not gonna be hard.

109
00:08:05,663 --> 00:08:07,226
Doesn't mean it's not gonna be confusing.

110
00:08:07,227 --> 00:08:11,319
But whatever it is, we'll face it together.

111
00:08:13,201 --> 00:08:15,551
You are quite charming, you know that?

112
00:08:15,552 --> 00:08:17,241
You haven't even seen my "a" game.

113
00:08:17,242 --> 00:08:19,413
Oh, lord, help me if that's true.

114
00:08:23,188 --> 00:08:25,175
It's Scott, by the way.

115
00:08:25,767 --> 00:08:28,137
You called me Haley James.

116
00:08:28,328 --> 00:08:30,737
Haley James Scott.

117
00:08:31,568 --> 00:08:33,348
And it always will be.

118
00:08:40,196 --> 00:08:42,107
Welcome back, students.

119
00:08:42,108 --> 00:08:45,644
Today as we return to our school with heavy hearts,

120
00:08:45,645 --> 00:08:47,620
