262
00:17:48,545 --> 00:17:50,379
Do I think there's a heaven?

263
00:17:50,938 --> 00:17:55,711
Yeah, you know, like the pearly gates, angels.

264
00:17:57,068 --> 00:17:58,988
I don't know about all that.

265
00:17:59,334 --> 00:18:03,190
Maybe some chrome gates and some freaky angels.

266
00:18:06,108 --> 00:18:10,404
No. But I do think there's something else out there.

267
00:18:10,867 --> 00:18:17,402
And I do think that whatever we do in this world matters in the next.

268
00:18:18,866 --> 00:18:22,118
Before you came in, I was thinking about Edwards...

269
00:18:24,181 --> 00:18:27,328
how he could take Keith's life.

270
00:18:27,329 --> 00:18:29,393
Look, he wasn't right, dog.

271
00:18:29,947 --> 00:18:31,242
Jimmy was sick.

272
00:18:31,243 --> 00:18:36,061
So if that's true, is heaven the kind of place that will hold that against someone?

273
00:18:36,062 --> 00:18:37,684
Because if not,

274
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:40,936
Jimmy's a victim, too.

275
00:18:41,407 --> 00:18:45,309
And right now in your world beyond this one,

276
00:18:45,310 --> 00:18:48,193
Jimmy and Keith are in the same place.

277
00:18:49,974 --> 00:18:52,647
I can't figure out what kind of place that would be.

278
00:18:52,648 --> 00:18:55,026
It's a place you and I wouldn't understand.

279
00:18:55,494 --> 00:18:57,638
Or a place that doesn't exist.

280
00:19:00,669 --> 00:19:02,393
Oh, I love this song.

281
00:19:07,228 --> 00:19:09,327
You think that's okay?

282
00:19:09,593 --> 00:19:14,233
To, like, love a song and feel good when you hear it

283
00:19:14,234 --> 00:19:18,049
and, like, laugh and be happy

284
00:19:19,107 --> 00:19:22,213
and be so in love with somebody your heart aches?

285
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:29,174
I mean, is that okay right now, or is it just too soon?

286
00:19:29,554 --> 00:19:33,234
It's never, never too soon to feel like that.

287
00:19:47,676 --> 00:19:49,470
Danny.

288
00:19:53,114 --> 00:19:55,292
Danny, I'm waiting.

289
00:19:56,058 --> 00:19:58,130
Why'd you do this to me?

290
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,728
I saw the light.

291
00:20:28,729 --> 00:20:30,063
I doubt it.

292
00:20:33,271 --> 00:20:35,280
Truth be told, I couldn't sleep.

293
00:20:37,181 --> 00:20:38,224
Can I help you?

294
00:20:38,225 --> 00:20:41,707
No, Dan. You can't help me.

295
00:20:44,099 --> 00:20:46,383
You were horrible to Keith.

296
00:20:47,287 --> 00:20:49,773
Is it any wonder you can't sleep?

297
00:20:49,813 --> 00:20:51,009
Doesn't mean I didn't love him.

298
00:20:51,010 --> 00:20:52,601
Well, that's great, Dan.

299
00:20:52,779 --> 00:20:55,687
But how's it feel to know you can never take any of it back?

300
00:20:55,688 --> 00:20:58,679
And for the rest of your life, all you'll have is regret

301
00:20:58,680 --> 00:21:03,100
over a relationship you could have repaired with a few kind words.

302
00:21:03,148 --> 00:21:06,344
But you couldn't even find it in your heart to do it.

303
00:21:06,649 --> 00:21:08,679
Maybe I'll find those words with Lucas.

304
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:12,326
No. Don't push me, Dan.

305
00:21:12,327 --> 00:21:15,796
Come on, Karen. He's old enough to make his own decisions.

306
00:21:15,797 --> 00:21:18,083
Like when he went back into that school,

307
00:21:18,085 --> 00:21:20,806
or when he pulled me out of the dealership fire.

308
00:21:32,008 --> 00:21:34,228
Did you pull Dan out of the fire?

309
00:21:35,665 --> 00:21:36,471
Mom --

310
00:21:36,472 --> 00:21:37,677
Did you?

311
00:21:40,131 --> 00:21:41,532
Yes.

312
00:21:43,179 --> 00:21:47,460
You selfish, stupid boy.

313
00:21:47,518 --> 00:21:49,490
Did you think about me?

314
00:21:49,491 --> 00:21:54,710
Just once think about me and what my life would be like if I lost you?

315
00:21:54,711 --> 00:21:58,233
Running into burning buildings, high schools with guns --

316
00:21:58,234 --> 00:22:00,035
did I raise an idiot?

317
00:22:00,036 --> 00:22:03,087
I know! Okay? I know! It's my fault!

318
00:22:03,088 --> 00:22:06,454
If I didn't go back in there, Keith would still be here.

319
00:22:06,537 --> 00:22:08,265
And I know that.

320
00:22:10,704 --> 00:22:12,123
And I'm sorry.

321
00:22:15,790 --> 00:22:20,872
Well, sorry isn't gonna bring him back, is it?

322
00:22:49,313 --> 00:22:51,169
You have to let it go, Mouth.

323
00:22:51,752 --> 00:22:53,387
It's not your fault.

324
00:22:54,333 --> 00:22:56,076
I wasn't thinking that.

325
00:22:56,987 --> 00:22:58,506
Yes, you were.

326
00:22:59,382 --> 00:23:02,033
You have this ridiculous notion that, because you were friends once,

327
00:23:02,034 --> 00:23:03,692
you could have saved him.

328
00:23:03,921 --> 00:23:06,095
What's so ridiculous about that?

329
00:23:07,077 --> 00:23:08,416
Because you couldn't have.

330
00:23:08,417 --> 00:23:10,373
I was his best friend, Rachel.

331
00:23:10,374 --> 00:23:12,999
How many times did the guy call you in the last year?

332
00:23:13,635 --> 00:23:15,443
Come on, look around.

333
00:23:15,503 --> 00:23:17,403
Everybody's here tonight.

334
00:23:17,404 --> 00:23:20,332
Geeks, stoners, jocks,

335
00:23:20,333 --> 00:23:23,461
maybe a few old friends who forgot to stay in touch.

336
00:23:24,197 --> 00:23:25,854
That's how it's gonna change.

337
00:23:25,855 --> 00:23:27,910
But everyone's still divided.

338
00:23:29,012 --> 00:23:33,207
We stick to these rigid circles of friends based on sports we play

339
00:23:33,208 --> 00:23:37,147
or hobbies we like or how attractive or unattractive we are.

340
00:23:37,425 --> 00:23:39,466
When's that gonna change?

341
00:23:39,467 --> 00:23:40,825
H onestly?

342
00:23:41,337 --> 00:23:42,747
Probably never.

343
00:23:43,591 --> 00:23:47,376
Look, that's human nature. People stick to their own kind.

344
00:23:47,377 --> 00:23:50,028
If you want it to change, then change it.

345
00:23:50,288 --> 00:23:51,649
I'll help you.

346
00:23:52,284 --> 00:23:53,660
How?

347
00:23:55,725 --> 00:23:57,082
Dance with me.

348
00:24:12,828 --> 00:24:13,856
Hey.

349
00:24:14,052 --> 00:24:15,112
Hey.

350
00:24:19,234 --> 00:24:20,330
Here.

351
00:24:20,868 --> 00:24:22,539
What is this?

352
00:24:22,540 --> 00:24:23,765
It's my door key.

353
00:24:23,766 --> 00:24:25,595
Actually it's your door key.

354
00:24:25,636 --> 00:24:27,756
- Brooke, it's your place.
- No.

355
00:24:27,757 --> 00:24:30,724
It's always been your place, both of yours.

356
00:24:31,014 --> 00:24:33,676
I was just keeping it warm till you came to your senses.

357
00:24:33,677 --> 00:24:34,748
Thank you, Brooke.

358
00:24:34,749 --> 00:24:35,916
Thanks.

359
00:24:36,946 --> 00:24:38,535
How's Lucas doing?

360
00:24:39,228 --> 00:24:40,966
I don't know. He left.

361
00:24:41,104 --> 00:24:44,170
Just trying to give him his space, but it's hard, you know?

362
00:24:44,806 --> 00:24:47,281
Anyway, you kids be happy.

363
00:24:47,282 --> 00:24:50,420
One of these days, you'll make the rest of us believe in true love.

364
00:24:53,300 --> 00:24:55,146
I want to go find Lucas.

365
00:24:55,389 --> 00:24:56,930
Okay, let's go.

366
00:24:57,627 --> 00:24:58,683
Okay.

367
00:25:01,647 --> 00:25:02,899
Hey, hold on.

368
00:26:28,462 --> 00:26:30,137
Why did you do that?

369
00:26:34,280 --> 00:26:37,679
Because I don't think you're gonna like me 10 seconds from now.

370
00:26:37,680 --> 00:26:38,703
But --

371
00:26:38,704 --> 00:26:40,740
I released the time capsule.

372
00:26:41,410 --> 00:26:43,549
It's not your fault, Mouth.

373
00:26:44,327 --> 00:26:45,662
It's mine.

374
00:26:52,503 --> 00:26:53,804
You're right.

375
00:26:55,518 --> 00:26:57,164
I don't like you.

376
00:27:19,329 --> 00:27:20,370
Hey.

377
00:27:23,143 --> 00:27:24,167
Here.

378
00:27:26,394 --> 00:27:28,729
I'm taking my predictions back.

379
00:27:29,318 --> 00:27:32,423
They're not gonna come true now, anyway, not without Keith.

380
00:27:32,902 --> 00:27:33,976
Luke.

381
00:27:34,152 --> 00:27:38,571
My mom thinks that this was my fault.

382
00:27:38,572 --> 00:27:39,927
She would not say that.

383
00:27:39,928 --> 00:27:41,680
Yeah, she pretty much did.

384
00:27:42,925 --> 00:27:44,866
We shouldn't have gone back into that school.

385
00:27:44,867 --> 00:27:46,344
She's wrong.

386
00:27:46,403 --> 00:27:49,059
Luke, Keith would have gone back into that school

387
00:27:49,060 --> 00:27:52,806
if you were in there or not because that is who he was.

388
00:27:53,282 --> 00:27:55,278
This is not your fault.

389
00:27:55,279 --> 00:27:57,652
She's right, Luke. You did what he did.

390
00:27:57,653 --> 00:27:59,981
You went back in there to save a life.

391
00:27:59,982 --> 00:28:01,866
Otherwise we might have been at Peyton's funeral.

392
00:28:01,867 --> 00:28:03,489
But I couldn't save Keith.

393
00:28:03,490 --> 00:28:04,923
Neither could I.

394
00:28:04,924 --> 00:28:08,225
He loved you a lot, Luke, just like we do.

395
00:28:09,219 --> 00:28:10,905
And so does Brooke.

396
00:28:11,523 --> 00:28:13,623
You think none of your predictions are gonna come true?

397
00:28:13,624 --> 00:28:15,632
Look at the first one on your list.

398
00:28:15,633 --> 00:28:19,009
"This year I'll try again with Brooke."

399
00:28:25,705 --> 00:28:26,980
Brooke?

400
00:28:28,496 --> 00:28:29,506
Brooke!

401
00:28:29,507 --> 00:28:30,828
She's gone.

402
00:28:32,850 --> 00:28:35,477
Coach, I can explain it all.

403
00:28:35,478 --> 00:28:41,180
It wouldn't matter, seeing as how I'm not here right now.

404
00:28:43,169 --> 00:28:45,906
Not that I approve of any of this, but...

405
00:28:45,977 --> 00:28:52,835
I guess kids getting drunk in school beats kids getting killed.

406
00:28:57,238 --> 00:28:59,124
Been meaning to talk to you.

407
00:28:59,664 --> 00:29:02,631
The truth of the matter is I've been busy...

408
00:29:02,908 --> 00:29:05,161
crying like a baby.

409
00:29:05,621 --> 00:29:07,589
They were gonna get married.

410
00:29:08,826 --> 00:29:10,612
Keith was gonna be my dad.

411
00:29:10,613 --> 00:29:12,497
He was your dad.

412
00:29:12,499 --> 00:29:15,605
No matter what any science or papers said.

413
00:29:15,606 --> 00:29:19,924
He was the man who influenced your life more than anybody else.

414
00:29:19,925 --> 00:29:22,281
I saw it in you every day.

415
00:29:22,610 --> 00:29:24,523
I just want him to come back.

416
00:29:25,330 --> 00:29:27,167
I just want him to come home.

417
00:29:28,468 --> 00:29:29,832
It's not fair.

418
00:29:31,501 --> 00:29:33,623
I'm gonna tell you something.

419
00:29:34,742 --> 00:29:39,232
When my wife... died,

420
00:29:39,690 --> 00:29:44,735
things got pretty dark there for a while.

421
00:29:44,825 --> 00:29:47,142
Nobody could talk to me.

422
00:29:48,203 --> 00:29:51,820
And then one of my former players --

423
00:29:52,517 --> 00:29:56,303
kid may have been the worst player I ever coached --

424
00:29:58,133 --> 00:30:00,638
waded into that darkness

425
00:30:01,504 --> 00:30:04,124
and pulled me to safety.

426
00:30:05,837 --> 00:30:10,329
Kid's name was Keith Scott.

427
00:30:13,851 --> 00:30:21,186
He said, "coach, I know you want some answers.

428
00:30:21,187 --> 00:30:23,524
But what is the right answer?

429
00:30:23,980 --> 00:30:26,623
Because there is no answer.

430
00:30:26,782 --> 00:30:28,775
There's just life."

431
00:30:29,173 --> 00:30:32,373
Just life.

432
00:30:33,829 --> 00:30:38,921
Lucas, be the man that Keith taught you to be.

433
00:30:39,153 --> 00:30:43,846
Anything less will make this a much greater tragedy than it already is.

434
00:30:56,316 --> 00:30:58,341
Danny.

435
00:31:00,891 --> 00:31:03,041
Why'd you do this to me?

436
00:31:04,993 --> 00:31:06,853
It's not gonna work, you know.

437
00:31:08,169 --> 00:31:10,735
I'm not gonna carry this around with me.

438
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:12,899
I did what I did, and it's done.

439
00:31:12,900 --> 00:31:14,517
Danny.

440
00:31:14,518 --> 00:31:17,363
So you come around all you want, ghost. You won't scare me.

441
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:24,665
As a matter of fact, tonight I'm gonna sleep like a baby. You want to know why?

442
00:31:26,747 --> 00:31:29,168
Because you started this war.

443
00:31:30,018 --> 00:31:31,796
I just finished it.

444
00:31:33,829 --> 00:31:35,533
I just finished it.

445
00:32:04,395 --> 00:32:07,200
This is Karen's wedding dress material.

446
00:32:11,001 --> 00:32:12,923
If only it were raining.

447
00:32:13,215 --> 00:32:14,821
I think I can take care of that.

448
00:32:16,188 --> 00:32:17,332
Come on.

449
00:32:23,993 --> 00:32:25,014
Hey.

450
00:32:25,015 --> 00:32:28,142
Do you know a Pete from "Freak Out Boy,"

451
00:32:28,143 --> 00:32:31,323
tattoos, goofy grin, about as tall as a fire hydrant?

452
00:32:31,324 --> 00:32:33,526
- Fall Out Boy.
- Yeah, whatever.

453
00:32:33,527 --> 00:32:36,807
I can't believe I'm about to say this to my high school-aged daughter,

454
00:32:36,808 --> 00:32:40,718
but he is waiting in that limo.

455
00:32:41,377 --> 00:32:44,776
Don't be long.

456
00:32:44,777 --> 00:32:46,029
Okay.

457
00:33:18,192 --> 00:33:19,795
I want you to know something.

458
00:33:21,016 --> 00:33:23,155
If anything ever happens to me,

459
00:33:23,156 --> 00:33:25,885
- if you ever lose me --
- Nathan.

460
00:33:25,886 --> 00:33:28,294
I want you to know how happy you made me,

461
00:33:29,054 --> 00:33:32,358
how wonderful my life was with you and...

462
00:33:32,799 --> 00:33:34,888
I will always be with you.

463
00:33:36,375 --> 00:33:38,130
Nothing's gonna happen to you.

464
00:33:38,131 --> 00:33:39,420
I know.

465
00:33:39,517 --> 00:33:44,179
I know. You're right. But if it does, I just --

466
00:33:44,367 --> 00:33:46,596
I want you to be okay, Haley,

467
00:33:47,067 --> 00:33:50,068
and know that you made me happy.

468
00:33:59,633 --> 00:34:01,101
You wanted rain.

469
00:34:04,556 --> 00:34:07,495
It is not possible to be this in love.

470
00:34:26,243 --> 00:34:27,805
Hey, pretty girl.

471
00:34:28,599 --> 00:34:29,834
Hey.

472
00:34:29,996 --> 00:34:32,633
I was gonna sleep in my car, but I heard a noise,

473
00:34:32,634 --> 00:34:34,901
and I think it was a bear or something.

474
00:34:34,902 --> 00:34:36,543
Well, where were you parked?

475
00:34:36,544 --> 00:34:38,993
Right outside here.

476
00:34:40,668 --> 00:34:45,302
Well, have I told you how much I love you today?

477
00:34:46,103 --> 00:34:47,577
Not really.

478
00:34:47,633 --> 00:34:49,206
Well, I do,

479
00:34:49,911 --> 00:34:53,957
and even when I don't tell you, it means a lot to me to know you're there.

480
00:34:54,133 --> 00:34:56,905
It means everything.

481
00:34:57,585 --> 00:34:59,526
I am here.

482
00:35:00,100 --> 00:35:01,758
We both are.

483
00:35:01,759 --> 00:35:03,106
I know.

484
00:35:03,288 --> 00:35:04,962
It's good being here...

485
00:35:06,078 --> 00:35:08,042
especially with you.

486
00:35:10,833 --> 00:35:12,819
I wished that it was me.

487
00:35:15,523 --> 00:35:19,213
I know that's horrible, and I know that's selfish, but...

488
00:35:20,296 --> 00:35:24,474
I watched you rescued Peyton, and you told me you rescued Dan.

489
00:35:24,475 --> 00:35:26,758
And sometimes I just wish you could rescue me.

490
00:35:26,759 --> 00:35:28,008
From what?

491
00:35:28,545 --> 00:35:30,084
From all of it.

492
00:35:31,217 --> 00:35:32,443
Okay, then.

493
00:35:33,810 --> 00:35:35,022
I will.

494
00:35:36,801 --> 00:35:40,459
If you promise to rescue me back.

495
00:35:41,383 --> 00:35:42,731
I promise.

496
00:35:49,924 --> 00:35:52,126
There's something else I need to do.

497
00:35:59,511 --> 00:36:01,506
- Hey, buddy.
- Hey.

498
00:36:02,426 --> 00:36:03,850
How's the leg?

499
00:36:03,851 --> 00:36:06,541
Oh, it'll be okay.

500
00:36:06,542 --> 00:36:08,055
How's the boy?

501
00:36:08,368 --> 00:36:10,002
It'll be okay.

502
00:36:10,348 --> 00:36:12,694
- Oh --
- I'm sorry, Peyton.

503
00:36:12,798 --> 00:36:13,951
Why?

504
00:36:15,004 --> 00:36:16,914
Because I shouldn't have left you there.

505
00:36:16,915 --> 00:36:18,520
I thought you were behind me.

506
00:36:18,521 --> 00:36:21,535
- Brooke, don't --
- No. I should have made sure.

507
00:36:21,536 --> 00:36:25,012
Okay. You're my best friend.

508
00:36:25,013 --> 00:36:29,998
And you want to know what made me feel better when I was trapped in that library?

509
00:36:29,999 --> 00:36:31,781
It was knowing that Brooke's okay, you know?

510
00:36:31,782 --> 00:36:33,957
My best friend, she's safe.

511
00:36:34,643 --> 00:36:37,200
I love you for that, P. Sawyer.

512
00:36:38,043 --> 00:36:42,096
But there was something else that made you feel better in that library --

513
00:36:42,309 --> 00:36:44,057
my boyfriend.

514
00:36:44,847 --> 00:36:47,261
And I guess I can't hold it against him, can I?

515
00:36:47,262 --> 00:36:51,758
I mean, the boy I love protected the girl I love.

516
00:36:52,802 --> 00:36:55,161
- And it's the girl that he loves, too.
- Brooke --

517
00:36:55,162 --> 00:36:57,400
No. We both know it's true.

518
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:01,095
Okay.

519
00:37:03,169 --> 00:37:05,492
- What --
- come here. No. Come here.

520
00:37:05,965 --> 00:37:09,408
All right. I want you to listen to me.

521
00:37:10,214 --> 00:37:13,980
I care about Lucas, and I always will.

522
00:37:14,669 --> 00:37:17,810
But he's insanely in love with you.

523
00:37:18,206 --> 00:37:20,420
And you know what? So am I.

524
00:37:20,435 --> 00:37:22,043
You're my Brooke.

525
00:37:23,180 --> 00:37:25,262
I'm not gonna hurt you again.

526
00:37:26,549 --> 00:37:29,384
Okay, 'cause I really don't want to hurt again.

527
00:37:29,622 --> 00:37:30,901
Come here. 

528
00:37:32,662 --> 00:37:34,601
